🧱 B01 — BLOCK 1 of 8 — Create table + primary column
What to do in the maker portal (make.powerapps.com → your dev environment):

Left nav → Tables → + New table → New table (the "Start from blank" option, NOT "Set advanced properties" first — the dialog has the primary column tab inline).
Properties tab of the new-table dialog:

Display name: Rule
Plural name: Rules  (should auto-fill; confirm)
Description: paste this verbatim →
Applicability rule — a single statement of when a control procedure applies, with its binary verdict, collection scope, priority, terminating flag, JSON expression, and plain-English rendering. Lifecycle: Draft → Active → (soft-delete to) Inactive. Versioning lives on the related pei_ruleversion table.
Schema name: confirm it auto-derived to pei_rule (the pei_ prefix is your publisher's default). If it shows anything else (e.g., new_rule), the publisher context is wrong — STOP and fix the publisher before proceeding.


Advanced options (expand the section if collapsed):

Type: Standard (NOT Activity, NOT Virtual)
Record ownership: User or team (NOT Organization)
Choose properties:

✅ Enable attachments (notes) — leave ON
❌ Activities — leave OFF
✅ Quick Create form — leave ON (we'll generate the form in Block 7)
✅ Audit changes — turn ON
(Other toggles like "Allow connections", "Allow feedback" — leave at defaults)




★ CRITICAL — Primary column tab (top of the dialog). Click into it BEFORE Save:

Display name: Rule Name
Watch the schema name field auto-derive to pei_rulename.
If the schema name shows pei_name or anything other than pei_rulename, edit it directly in the schema name field to pei_rulename and confirm before Save.
Data type: Single line of text (the default — Text)
Required: Business required
Maximum character count: 100 (default)
Searchable: leave ON (default)


Verify before clicking Save:

Display name reads Rule
Schema name reads pei_rule
Primary column display reads Rule Name
Primary column schema reads pei_rulename  ← this is the one that locks at save
Ownership = User or team
Audit changes = ON


Click Save. Wait for the table-creation spinner to finish and the new-table page to open.

Why this matters: Once the table is saved, the primary column's logical/schema name cannot be renamed — only dropped-and-recreated by dropping the table. The L1-A02 anti-pattern (pei_Name on pei_buorgunitmapping) was exactly this slip. Getting pei_rulename set BEFORE Save is the entire purpose of this block.

